      "date": "2018-04-16 22:50:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nI'm not a super fan of version-based checks, but I don't see a great alternative.  At least this is something that can be removed fairly easily in the future once we don't care about older server compatibility.\n\nShould this be wrapped in:\n\n #ifdef LUSTRE_VERSION_CODE < OBD_OCD_VERSION(3, 0, 53)\n #endif\n\nso that at a certain point it is clear that this can be removed?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
